programme.title: Far Flung with Gary Mehigan
programme.desc:
Join popular Masterchef Australia judge and chef Gary Mehigan as he explores his twin passions for fine food and fast bikes, on this six-part culinary road trip through Asia. From the spice markets of Delhi to the street stalls of Vietnam, Gary proves a knowledgeable and enthusiastic guide to each area’s produce and cooking methods, championing food artisans, producers and stall holders in markets around the world.
The series starts in India where Gary heads to Mumbai to cook his own Tiffin box lunch before discovering herbs and spices even he’s never heard of at the world’s largest market in Delhi. In Jodhpur he attends the Maharaja’s Full Moon dinner and learns from his chef how to cook for thousands of Riff Festival revellers before heading to Chennai for a tour of the local fish markets and the chance to kick back and cook on the beach.
The series then heads to Vietnam, Laos, South Korea and Hong Kong. Among the highlights: cooking alms for the local monks in Luang Prabang in Laos and attempting to run his own rice taco stall in Ho Chi Minh City.
Far Flung is more than just a cookery show, however, as Gary’s pleasure in meeting new people and trying new things combines with his need for speed to create six vivid travel diaries. Whether visiting Chennai’s Royal Enfield Factory or meeting the man transforming lives with scooters, Gary’s warmth and wit shine through making him an invaluable companion on this fascinating journey through the far flung markets of the world.

programme.title: The Cook’s Pantry with Matt Sinclair Season 1
programme.desc: From an early age, Matt knew he wanted to create something unique with his food. From the suburbs of Sydney, Matty spent over a decade working in hospitality. Here he evolved a curiosity of the industry, and the desire to work with food as a career. This saw him audition for MasterChef, where he quickly became a household favourite, triumphing as the 2016 runner up. Shortly after, Matt’s dream to own a successful food truck business came true. The quick growth and success saw their business grow into a fullyfledged restaurant in Noosa on the Sunshine Coast. The Cooks Pantry is a weekly cooking show that celebrates the creation of wholesome Australian food. Join Matt Sinclair and his fellow foodies Courtney Roulston and Michael Weldon. As successful MasterChef contestants, the team combine together to help you create simple, delicious food.

programme.desc: Katie Says Goodbye' is the heart-wrenching story of an optimistic and kind-hearted young woman named Katie whose life takes a dramatic turn when a new romance blossoms. Living in a struggling desert town in Arizona composed of little more than a trailer park and a small diner, Katie (Olivia Cooke) dreams of a new life in San Francisco. In order to best save the necessary funds to leave her desolate town and start anew, Katie prostitutes herself to a handful of regulars that frequent the diner she waitresses at. As Katie draws near to saving the funds she believes her new life requires, she encounters a young ex-convict named Bruno (Christopher Abbott).

programme.title: Burn Country
programme.desc: After being exiled from Afghanistan, a former war journalist settles in a small town in Northern California and takes a job with a local newspaper. But when he attempts to cover a crime, he stumbles into local corruption under the surface that puts himself and others in danger.

programme.title: Stone
programme.desc: Academy-Award winner Robert De Niro and Academy-Award nominee Edward Norton deliver powerful performances as a seasoned corrections official and a scheming inmate whose lives become dangerously intertwined in this thought-provoking drama.

programme.title: Invasion Planet Earth
programme.desc: After the death of his young daughter, Tom Dunn is a broken man. When his wife falls pregnant again, he cannot believe their luck. However, his joy is short-lived, as, on the very same day, the people of Earth become plagued with terrifying visions of the end of the world. When a gigantic, all-consuming alien mothership appears in the sky and launches a ruthless attack on Earth's cities, chaos and destruction follow. Tom must find the strength and wisdom to save his wife and unborn child. However, first he must confront a shocking truth. A truth which threatens the key to the survival of the human race. The ultimate war for Planet Earth is about to begin...

From the producers of 'Bone Tomahawk' and 'The Hurt Locker'.

programme.title: Robert The Bruce
programme.desc: Robert the Bruce is a hard-hitting historical epic covering the turbulent time after William Wallace's victories depicted in Braveheart. Scotland 1306, Robert the Bruce crowns himself King and takes the ambition of Scotland's freedom as his own. But he cannot overcome England's power: defeated, again and again, his army is scattered and Scotland's nobility abandons him. Hunted, with a price on his head, he finds himself alone and wounded. The cause of freedom seems lost once more. Hidden secretly in a secluded croft of a clan pledged to England, and close to death, Robert is nursed back to life by a young widow and her orphaned children.

programme.desc: John "Falcon" Chapman, is an ex-marine anti-hero plagued with a terrible secret consuming him with guilt. On the self-destructive edge, he learns his sister Cindy has been brutally beaten in the slums or "favelas" of Brazil and travels there to hunt down her attackers. In the process he discovers an underground world of drugs, prostitution, and police corruption ruled by the Japanese mafia and protected by the powerful Hirimoto. Can Chapman overcome his personal demons when tracking down his sister's attacker, or will he become another casualty?
